Public BioCyc Data File Downloads

  • For each organism (database) in the BioCyc collection, we provide a set of data files. In some cases the same information is available in multiple formats.
    Descriptions of the formats of most files in this directory are at: http://bioinformatics.ai.sri.com/ptools/flatfile-format.html
  • When downloading databases, you can choose between tar.gz and zip archive formats. Each single-database archive contains the set of data files for that database.
    For example, to download a database as a tar.gz archive, click on Download tar.gz column for that organism.
